				I quit EQ and started playing DAoC.  I have to say I am less than thrilled with DAoC.  I keep comparing it to EQ and in my opinion it doesnt even come close.  However, DAoC did do one thing right, and that is the downtime between fights. <br>  <br> I know I am probably beating a dead horse.  I just have to say, one of the main reasons I left EQ is because I couldnt take getting into a fight and then having to sit and stare at my computer for a long time before I was ready to fight again.  Its a blatant acknowledgement from EQ when they make a mini game that players can play while they are resting up between fights, that something is wrong with the system. <br>  <br> Please, please EQ make the down time a little shorter, how can that affect the game in a negative way?  Do this one simple thing and I will be back for good, never to leave again. <br>  <br> Window		

