			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				what would get me back to EQ here's a few: <br> 1, All teleportation spells to be removed <br> 2, Boats to have bars pirates raids sea monster attacks storms etc.  <br> 3, RvR in all but the newbie zones <br> 4, Temperature forcing players to wear appropriate clothing and seasonal changes. <br> 5, The buildings to be a place of refuge that one can rest or hide in, or hunt from. <br> 6, The removal of all those crazy uber fabulous weapons/items and spells like res. <br> 7, The emphasis moved away from the level based system  <br> 8, life span for characters with ageing and appropriate stat changes where STR and DEX give way to WIZ and say better trade skills. <br> 9, Territory gains for some races evolving a story  <br> 10, XP not to be used as the death penalty something more realistic like premature ageing and having your corpse player lootable.  <br> 11, Twinking to be recognised as a good thing. (giving your friend a half decent weapon and a bit of armour is a nice thing) <br> 12, Removal of the never ending vendor supplies to be replaced with player made supplies made with trade skills  <br> 13, Random spawn sites and levels  <br> 14, Run to reduce STA seriously (no SOW) what&#8217;s the point in making zones big when speed keeps increasing ? <br> 15, Horses, donkeys, pet dogs which you can rename and are persistent, there when you log on <br> 16, Lots more animated emotes lots more ! with facial expressions <br> 17, Less death ! with the ability to beat or be beaten close to death especially by NPC&#8217;s or players of the same faction. <br>   <br> I hope I&#8217;m talking EQ2 here <br> Cos it would be hell of a patch <img src="/images/faces/happy.gif" border=0 alt="happy.gif" height=18 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0>  <br>  <br>   		

