				I too miss the sheer awe of EQ while playing DAoC. I have a busy rl and long for a game like EQ, but that I could play for a couple of hours every now and then. DAoC works well for that by gaining exp &quot;doing your own thing&quot; and then when you have the time I can find a group do some RvR or kill purple mobs (Red mobs for you EQ'ers). I gave my EQ account away due to the agonizing frustration in playing EQ in the high 40's, but now I'm thinking of buying EQ again and starting over (with some twinking from some friends of course <img src="/images/faces/happy.gif" border=0 alt="happy.gif" height=18 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0>  ). However I get all psyched to start again, but then cringe when I think of the Hell levels. If they could fix those I'd probably get into it again. After playing 5 characters to upper 40's, I just don't think I can bare another sub 50 hell level <img src="/images/faces/sad.gif" border=0 alt="sad.gif" height=18 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0> 		

